born_year         = 1973\n| died_year         = \n| term_start        = 21 September 2019\n| timeinoffice      = {{age in years and days|2019|09|21}} \n}}\n{{Officeholder table end}}\n\n===Origin of the name===\nThe fact that the major centre-right political party in a country calls itself 'Left' is often confusing to foreign (and sometimes Danish) observers. The name has, however, its historical explanation. At the time of its foundation, ''Venstre'' affirmed then-progressive ideas in the Danish parliament. Their opponents, ''H\u00f8jre'' (Right), the forerunner of the present-day [[Conservative People's Party (Denmark)|Conservative People's Party]], advocated for established interests, particularly the [[Church of Denmark]] and the landed gentry. In current Danish politics there is a clear distinction between the concepts of ''Venstre'' (Left, i.e., the party bearing that name) and ''venstrefl\u00f8j'' (left wing, i.e., socialist and other left-leaning parties). The use of the word for \"left\" in the name of the Danish political party ''[[Det Radikale Venstre|Radikale Venstre]]'' and the [[Norway|Norwegian]] party ''[[Venstre (Norway)|Venstre]]'' is meant to refer to [[liberalism]] and not [[socialism]].\n\nMembers of the party are referred to as ''venstrem\u00e6nd'' and ''venstrekvinder'', respectively \"Venstre men\" and \"Venstre women\" (singular: -mand, -kvinde).\n\n==Election results==\n\n===Parliament===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Election year\n! # of overall votes\n! % of overall vote\n! % of Danish vote\n! # of overall seats won\n! # of Danish seats won\n! +/-\n! Notes\n|-\n! '''[[1872 Danish Folketing election|1872]]'''\n|\n| colspan=\"2\"|\n|colspan=\"2\"| {{Composition bar|53|104|hex=#25587E}}\n| ''New''\n| In ''Det Forenede Venstre.''\n|-\n! '''[[1873 Danish Folketing election|1873]]'''\n|\n| colspan=\"2\"|\n|colspan=\"2\"| {{Composition bar|51|104|hex=#25587E}}\n| {{decrease}} 2\n| In ''Det Forenede Venstre.''\n|-\n! '''[[1876 Danish Folketing 