born_year         = 1941\n| died_year         = \n| term_start        = 23 July 1984\n| term_end          = 18 March 1998\n| timeinoffice      = {{ayd|1984|07|23|1998|03|18}} \n}}\n{{Officeholder table\n| order             = 8\n| image             = Former Danish Prime Minister Anders Fogh Rasmussen at the Nordic Council Session in Helsinki 2008-10-28.jpg |bSize = 85px\n| officeholder      = [[Anders Fogh Rasmussen]]\n| officeholder_sort = Rasmussen, Anders\n| born_year         = 1953\n| died_year         = \n| term_start        = 18 March 1998\n| term_end          = 17 May 2009\n| timeinoffice      = {{age in years and days|1998|03|18|2009|05|17}} \n}}\n{{Officeholder table\n| order             = 9\n| image             = Lars L\u00f8kke Rasmussen - 2018 (MUS6631) (cropped).jpg |bSize = 85px\n| officeholder      = [[Lars L\u00f8kke Rasmussen]]\n| officeholder_sort = Rasmussen, Lars\n| born_year         = 1964\n| died_year         = \n| term_start        = 17 May 2009\n| term_end          = 31 August 2019\n| timeinoffice      = {{age in years and days|2009|5|17|2019|8|31}}\n}}\n{{Officeholder table\n| order             = \u2013\n| image             = Kristian Jensen, 25-05-2014.jpg |bSize = 85px\n| officeholder      = [[Kristian Jensen]]\n| officeholder_sort = Jensen, Kristian\n| born_year         = 1971\n| died_year         = \n| term_start        = 31 August 2019\n| term_end          = 21 September 2019\n| timeinoffice      = {{ayd|2019|08|31|2019|09|21}}\n| acting            = y\n}}\n{{Officeholder table\n| order             = 10\n| image             = Jakob Ellemann-Jensen 1.jpg |bSize = 85px\n| officeholder      = [[Jakob Ellemann-Jensen]]\n| officeholder_sort = Jensen, Kristian\n| born_year         = 1973\n| died_year         = \n| term_start        = 21 September 2019\n| timeinoffice      = {{age in years and days|2019|09|21}} \n}}\n{{Officeholder table end}}\n\n===Origin of the name===\nThe fact that the major centre-right political party in a country calls itself 'Left' is often confusing to foreign (and sometimes Danish) observers. The name has, however, its historical explanation. At the time of its foundation, ''Venstre'' affirmed then-progressive ideas in the Danish parliament. Their opponents, ''H\u00f8jre'' (Right), the forerunner of the present-day [[Conservative People's Party (Denmark)|Conservative People's Party]], advocated for established interests, particularly the [[Church of Denmark]] and the landed gentry. In current Danish politics there is a clear distinction between the concepts of ''Venstre'' (Left, i.e., the party bearing that name) and ''venstrefl\u00f8j'' (left wing, i.e., socialist and other left-leaning parties). The use of the word for \"left\" in the name of the Danish political party ''[[Det Radikale Venstre|Radikale Venstre]]'' and the [[Norway|Norwegian]] party ''[[Venstre (Norway)|Venstre]]'' is meant to refer to [[liberalism]] and not [[socialism]].\n\nMembers of the party are referred to as ''venstrem\u00e6nd'' and ''venstrekvinder'', respectively \"Venstre men\" and \"Venstre women\" (singular: -mand, -kvinde).\n\n==Election results==\n\n===Parliament===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Election year\n! # of overall votes\n! % of overall vote\n! % of Danish vote\n! # of overall seats won\n! # of Danish seats won\n! +/-\n! Notes\n|-\n! '''[[1872 Danish Folketing election|1872]]'''\n|\n| colspan=\"2\"|\n|colspan=\"2\"| {{Composition bar|53|104|hex=#25587E}}\n| ''New''\n| In ''Det Forenede Venstre.''\n|-\n! '''[[1873 Danish Folketing election|1873]]'''\n|\n| colspan=\"2\"|\n|colspan=\"2\"| {{Composition bar|51|104|hex=#25587E}}\n| {{decrease}} 2\n| In ''Det Forenede Venstre.''\n|-\n! '''[[1876 Danish Folketing election|1876]]'''\n|\n| colspan=\"2\"|\n|colspan=\"2\"| {{Composition bar|74|104|hex=#25587E}}\n| {{increase}} 23\n| In ''Folketingets Venstre.''\n|-\n! '''[[1879 Danish Folketing election|1879]]'''\n|\n| colspan=\"2\"|\n|colspan=\"2\"| {{Composition bar|65|104|hex=#25587E}}\n| {{decrease}} 9\n| In ''Folketingets Venstre.''\n|-\n! '''[[May 1881 Danish Folketing election|1881 (may)]]'''\n|\n| colspan=\"2\"|\n|colspan=\"2\"| {{Composition bar|69|102|hex=#25587E}}\n| {{increase}} 4\n| In ''Folketingets Venstre.''\n|-\n! '''[[July 1881 Danish Folketing election|1881 (jul)]]'''\n|\n| colspan=\"2\"|\n|colspan=\"2\"| {{Composition bar|75|102|hex=#25587E}}\n| {{increase}} 6\n| In ''Folketingets Venstre.''\n|-\n! '''[[1884 Danish Folketing election|1884]]'''\n| 80,000\n| colspan=\"2\"|56.3 (#1)\n|colspan=\"2\"| {{Composition bar|81|102|hex=#25587E}}\n| {{increase}} 6\n| In ''Venstre Reform Party.''\n|-\n! '''[[1887 Danish Folketing election|1887]]'''\n| 132,000\n| colspan=\"2\"|58.1 (#1)\n|colspan=\"2\"| {{Composition bar|74|102|hex=#25587E}}\n| {{decrease}} 7\n| In ''Venstre Reform Party.''\n|-\n! '''[[1890 Danish Folketing election|1890]]'''\n| 123,000\n| colspan=\"2\"|53.0 (#1)\n|colspan=\"2\"| {{Composition bar|75|102|hex=#25587E}}\n| {{increase}} 1\n| In ''Venstre Reform Party.''\n|-\n! '''[[1892 Danish Folketing election|1892]]'''\n| 63,000\n| colspan=\"2\"|28.1 (#3)\n|colspan=\"2\"| {{Composition bar|30|102|hex=#25587E}}\n| {{decrease}} 45\n| In ''Venstre Reform Party.''\n|-\n! '''[[1895 Danish Folketing election|1895]]'''\n| 89,530\n| colspan=\"2\"|40.5 (#1)\n|colspan=\"2\"| {{Composition bar|53|114|hex=#25587E}}\n| {{increase}} 23\n| In ''Venstre Reform Party.''\n|-\n! '''[[1898 Danish Folketing election|1898]]'''\n| 98,070\n| colspan=\"2\"|43.6 (#1)\n|colspan=\"2\"| {{Composition bar|63|114|hex=#25587E}}\n| {{increase}} 10\n| In ''Venstre Reform Party.''\n|-\n! '''[[1901 Danish Folketing election|1901]]'''\n| 103,495\n| colspan=\"2\"|45.9 (#1)\n|colspan=\"2\"| {{Composition bar|76|114|hex=#25587E}}\n| {{increase}} 13\n| In ''Venstre Reform Party.''\n|-\n! '''[[1903 Danish Folketing election|1903]]'''\n| 121,357\n| colspan=\"2\"|49.4 (#1)\n|colspan=\"2\"| {{Composition bar|73|114|hex=#25587E}}\n| {{decrease}} 3\n| In ''Venstre Reform Party.''\n